abstract: Allowing China's state-run rail construction company to build a high-speed rail line linking London with central and northern England would be an “extremely questionable" decision, a prominent British lawmaker said Saturday.
snippet: Allowing China's state-run rail construction company to build a high-speed rail line linking London with central and northern England would be an “extremely questionable" decision, a prominent British lawmaker said Saturday.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Allowing China's state-run rail construction company to build a high-speed rail line linking London with central and northern England would be an “extremely questionable" decision, a prominent British lawmaker said Saturday.
headline_main: Lawmaker Questions China's Offer to Build UK High Speed Rail
headline_print_headline: Lawmaker Questions China's Offer to Build UK High Speed Rail

abstract: The Trump administration is deploying highly trained officers to boost arrests of unauthorized immigrants in a number of cities, including Los Angeles, Chicago and New York, the latest move in a battle against localities that adopt "sanctuary" policies to protect them from deportation.
snippet: The Trump administration is deploying highly trained officers to boost arrests of unauthorized immigrants in a number of cities, including Los Angeles, Chicago and New York, the latest move in a battle against localities that adopt "sanctuary" pol...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration is deploying highly trained officers to boost arrests of unauthorized immigrants in a number of cities, including Los Angeles, Chicago and New York, the latest move in a battle against localities that adopt "sanctuary" policies to protect them from deportation.
headline_main: U.S. Border Patrol to Send Tactical Unit Officers to 'Sanctuary Cities'
headline_print_headline: U.S. Border Patrol to Send Tactical Unit Officers to 'Sanctuary Cities'

abstract: U.S. Defense Secretary Mark Esper on Saturday cast China as a rising threat to world order — saying the world's most populous nation steals Western know-how, intimidates smaller neighbors and seeks an “advantage by any means and at any cost.”
snippet: U.S. Defense Secretary Mark Esper on Saturday cast China as a rising threat to world order — saying the world's most populous nation steals Western know-how, intimidates smaller neighbors and seeks an “advantage by any means and at any cost.”
lead_paragraph: MUNICH — U.S. Defense Secretary Mark Esper on Saturday cast China as a rising threat to world order — saying the world's most populous nation steals Western know-how, intimidates smaller neighbors and seeks an “advantage by any means and at any cost.”
headline_main: US Defense Chief Slams China as Rising Threat to World Order
headline_print_headline: US Defense Chief Slams China as Rising Threat to World Order

abstract: Stars have retired or are poised to, leaving the sport struggling to get a foothold in the sports landscape.
snippet: Stars have retired or are poised to, leaving the sport struggling to get a foothold in the sports landscape.
lead_paragraph: As NASCAR readies for its first, and most important, event of the year, the Daytona 500 on Sunday, it sits at a crossroads. It has hundreds of thousands of passionate and fiercely loyal fans. But the days when it was on the brink of joining the major American sports seem past.
